What you need to know:

The 0-0 stalemate at St James' Park means the champions go into the New Year with a three-point lead over Manchester United, having played a game moreMohamed Salah - top of the Premier League goalscoring charts with 13 goals - missed the target either side of half-time with just goalkeeper Karl Darlow to beat and strike-partner Roberto Firmino saw two headers superbly savedKlopp's men finish the calendar year on 33 points from 16 games, three clear of United, who have 30 points after 15 matches